WEBVTT

00:03.738 --> 00:05.906
(subway train clacking)

00:07.000 --> 00:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:10.271 --> 01:12.172
All right,
everybody listen up!

01:12.940 --> 01:14.641
Everybody knows what time it is!

01:14.642 --> 01:16.509
All the belongings
in the bag.

01:16.510 --> 01:19.145
Good work, Handsome.

01:19.146 --> 01:21.548
Handsome regulates
the neighborhood!

01:21.549 --> 01:24.718
If you want to ride
my train, you pay my toll.

01:24.719 --> 01:27.354
Turn around! Turn around!
Let me get your watch!

01:27.355 --> 01:29.089
Turn around!
Turn around!

01:29.090 --> 01:30.757
(groaning)

01:46.774 --> 01:48.942
(gunshots)

01:51.846 --> 01:54.014
(plastic creaks, cracks)

01:54.615 --> 01:55.849
HENRY:
Don't force it.

01:55.850 --> 01:56.950
I'm not forcing it.

01:56.951 --> 01:59.819
It says a ten-year-old
can assemble this thing.

01:59.820 --> 02:01.855
I bet your wife
could assemble it.

02:01.856 --> 02:04.357
Dad, why don't you give
me hand here, please?

02:04.358 --> 02:07.260
You need a degree in mechanical
engineering for that.

02:07.261 --> 02:08.828
No kidding.

02:10.297 --> 02:11.398
FRANK:
How'd it go?

02:11.399 --> 02:14.267
Aha! My favorite
granddaughter.

02:14.268 --> 02:15.368
Your only granddaughter.

02:15.369 --> 02:17.203
Oh, you still playing
with toys, Danny?

02:17.204 --> 02:19.372
That's cute.
It's for my son's birthday.

02:19.373 --> 02:21.674
Well, if Mom were still
alive, she'd tell you

02:21.675 --> 02:23.076
that was beyond your skill set.

02:23.077 --> 02:24.377
DANNY: That's funny.
Ha, ha, ha.

02:24.378 --> 02:25.512
Wanna help?

02:26.480 --> 02:28.281
Hey, the whole
gang's here.

02:28.282 --> 02:29.149
Hey, Jamie.

02:29.150 --> 02:30.150
Hey, will you help me

02:30.151 --> 02:31.051
out here, college boy?

02:31.052 --> 02:32.218
You're pathetic.

02:32.219 --> 02:35.388
It says it's supposed
to lock in.

02:35.389 --> 02:37.257
Let me see this.

02:41.262 --> 02:44.164
Glad you came over.
You okay?

02:44.165 --> 02:45.131
Yeah. Fine.

02:45.132 --> 02:46.299
Boy, that's a relief.

02:46.300 --> 02:47.934
'Cause if I were
going through a divorce

02:47.935 --> 02:50.003
and my kid went on a
long trip with her father,

02:50.004 --> 02:51.237
and I had
to say goodbye,

02:51.238 --> 02:53.373
I wouldn't be fine.

02:54.175 --> 02:55.308
I'll have a scotch.

02:58.879 --> 03:00.980
She's just so happy about it.

03:00.981 --> 03:03.183
Is it a nice trip?

03:03.184 --> 03:04.651
Yeah. He's taking her
to San Francisco.

03:04.652 --> 03:06.152
But he doesn't even
like San Francisco.

03:06.153 --> 03:07.454
Sounds like a nice trip.

03:07.455 --> 03:09.589
(phone rings)

03:12.660 --> 03:14.227
Hold that thought.

03:14.228 --> 03:15.962
Yeah?

03:15.963 --> 03:18.131
What, when, and where?

03:18.132 --> 03:19.666
(phone buzzing)

03:19.667 --> 03:21.067
Oh, those damn things.

03:21.068 --> 03:22.102
Reagan.

03:22.103 --> 03:23.303
JAMIE: This is starting
to hurt my head.

03:23.304 --> 03:24.237
Yeah. Hey, you're gonna have

03:24.238 --> 03:25.438
to finish that on your own.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.907
Hey, I gotta work--
I gotta work at midnight.

03:27.908 --> 03:29.042
I'm supposed to leave
five minutes ago.

03:29.043 --> 03:31.211
See you Sunday, Grandpa.

03:31.212 --> 03:33.413
First platoon.
A rookie's lot.

03:33.414 --> 03:35.715
Yeah, I understand.

03:35.716 --> 03:38.585
I want regular updates, I want a
breakdown of all the injuries,

03:38.586 --> 03:40.320
and I want to know
who's assigned...

03:40.321 --> 03:42.555
Hey.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.791
Hey, a little
help here!

03:47.361 --> 03:49.596
(distant sirens wailing,
indistinct chatter)

03:52.766 --> 03:54.134
Hey.

03:58.272 --> 04:00.039
What do we got?

04:00.040 --> 04:02.609
Six perps, box cutters
and knives, one gun, one camera.

04:02.610 --> 04:04.978
We're still sorting out
the specifics of the mayhem.

04:04.979 --> 04:06.079
What's with the camera?

04:06.080 --> 04:07.747
They were recording
everything.

04:07.748 --> 04:09.048
It's a good
conversation piece.

04:09.049 --> 04:11.217
Break out the wilding video
at your dinner party.

04:11.218 --> 04:12.452
Who pulled the cord?

04:12.453 --> 04:13.653
Passengers
in the next car.

04:13.654 --> 04:15.588
They heard the gunshots,
saw what was happening

04:15.589 --> 04:17.724
through the storm windows,
did the right thing.

04:17.725 --> 04:19.125
Everybody scrambles
to the platform.

04:19.125 --> 04:21.861
Looks like from the blood,
they might have, uh, fled down

04:21.862 --> 04:23.196
to the tracks.
Yeah, I know.

04:23.197 --> 04:24.864
Clerks didn't see 'em
go out either exit.

04:24.865 --> 04:27.200
Got uniforms covering
two stations-- north and south.

04:27.201 --> 04:29.802
ESU and Canine are en route
to sweep the tunnels.

04:30.638 --> 04:32.438
A lot of blood.

04:32.439 --> 04:35.241
AVA: Yeah. We still don't
know why the shooting started

04:35.242 --> 04:36.509
or where the
bullets went.

04:36.510 --> 04:37.911
Recovered two
casings from a nine,

04:37.912 --> 04:40.146
and I got anti-crime
canvassing the hospitals.

04:40.147 --> 04:42.882
No passengers were shot,
as far as we know.

04:42.883 --> 04:44.951
Hey, where you going?

04:44.952 --> 04:48.254
I'm gonna go make myself useful.

04:48.255 --> 04:49.322
(sirens wailing)

04:49.323 --> 04:52.292
JAMIE:
Hey, Danny!

04:52.293 --> 04:54.060
Hey! Little brother!

04:54.061 --> 04:55.395
What are you
doing here?

04:55.396 --> 04:57.564
We got a prisoner
drop-off at the six-five.

04:57.565 --> 04:59.899
Yeah, thought I'd show the
rookie what a caper looks like.

04:59.900 --> 05:02.068
Bunch of cops rubbernecking,
looking to poach a collar, huh?

05:02.069 --> 05:04.304
Nah. Hey, my partner's gonna
be down there for a while.

05:04.305 --> 05:06.573
She's got the car keys.
You guys mind giving me a ride?

05:06.574 --> 05:08.374
Yeah, where to?
To the two train.

05:08.375 --> 05:09.742
It's got an emergency
exit over there,

05:09.743 --> 05:11.211
near the playground
between Beverly and Church.

05:11.212 --> 05:12.345
Just gonna make sure
it's not popped.

05:12.346 --> 05:13.713
JAMIE:
You think that's how

05:13.714 --> 05:15.081
they got out of the tunnel?

05:15.082 --> 05:16.449
Uh-huh.
All right, come on.

05:16.450 --> 05:18.117
Get in.

05:19.553 --> 05:21.988
So, Sarge, you taking good care
of my little brother?

05:21.989 --> 05:24.557
Yup. First thing I told him was
to imagine what you'd do,

05:24.558 --> 05:25.692
and then do the opposite.

05:25.693 --> 05:26.726
Wow. That's good advice.

05:26.727 --> 05:27.894
Now, if you just go straight

05:27.895 --> 05:28.928
on Nostrand,
we'll get there quicker.

05:28.929 --> 05:30.163
Hey, college boy,

05:30.164 --> 05:32.398
tell your brother the first rule
of riding in my car.

05:32.399 --> 05:34.167
Jamie, tell your boss
I know Brooklyn

05:34.168 --> 05:35.568
better than a Manhattan cop.

05:35.569 --> 05:37.470
This is me, keeping
my mouth shut.

05:37.471 --> 05:38.972
See? He's already
doing the opposite.

05:38.973 --> 05:40.873
That a boy, kid.

05:40.874 --> 05:42.175
He's learning quick.

05:42.176 --> 05:44.444
Son of a bitch!

05:44.445 --> 05:48.281
DANNY: <i>Looks like they popped</i>
<i>the subway hatch. Stop the car.</i>

05:52.353 --> 05:53.853
They're already
out of the tunnel.

05:53.854 --> 05:55.655
Hey, I got blood.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.023
DANNY:
It's not footprints, either.

05:57.024 --> 05:58.258
Somebody must be hurt.

05:58.259 --> 05:59.659
Hey, slow down, kid.

05:59.660 --> 06:02.028
12 sergeant, need
a 10-85 forthwith

06:02.029 --> 06:03.229
at Nostrand
and Tilden.

06:03.230 --> 06:05.198
Hey, kid.
I'm the lead.

06:05.199 --> 06:06.733
Hey!

06:06.734 --> 06:09.002
Police! Let me see your hands.

06:09.003 --> 06:11.704
Let me see
your hands!

06:11.705 --> 06:13.873
Put your hands in front!

06:16.744 --> 06:19.345
Hands up!

06:19.346 --> 06:21.147
Hey.

06:30.224 --> 06:31.691
RENZULLI: This guy's gone.
Looks like he bled out

06:31.692 --> 06:33.026
from under the stomach.
Yeah.

06:33.027 --> 06:34.827
RENZULLI:
Buddies left him behind.

06:34.828 --> 06:35.995
They left him to die.

06:35.996 --> 06:38.698
Says a lot about who
we're dealing with.

